<p>So I use AWS Amazon Cloudfront as my CDN, and I remember when installing W3 that there was a suggestion (in some online tutorial) that I should hold off activating the CDN until I finished my website. I did it as instructed!</p>
<p>But that was a few months ago, and eventually the website evolved and some of the design became more robust. I am noticing a slow down on the load time (which is normal  since I added a few things). However, I would like to make sure that the CDN is being effective and efficient.</p>
<p>My question is: should I use the Purge Tool and reconfigure? If not, when should I use the Purge Tool? I have never used it.</p>
<p>Also, how can I ensure that the CDN is configured correctly? I configured it once, but I never gave it much thought.</p>
<p>My website is <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://www.elementsofcinema.com">http://www.elementsofcinema.com</a> Thank you in advance. </p>
<p>Gabriel</p>
